#: ../../../release_details/9.6/refactor-amr-datamodel.md:1
msgid "Refactor of the AMR data model"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/refactor-amr-datamodel.md:3
msgid ""
"The AMR data model has been refactored for future proofing. "
"vtkUniformGridAMR now inherits from vtkPartitionedDataSetCollection instead "
"of vtkCompositeDataSet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/refactor-amr-datamodel.md:6
msgid ""
"This lets classes interact with AMR data as they would with any data object "
"tree or pdc when accessing data, without requiring specific code. Specific "
"code can and will still be needed in certain cases. Of course, when setting "
"up the AMR, the AMR API should be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/refactor-amr-datamodel.md:10
msgid ""
"Indeed, each AMR level is now stored as a vtkPartitionedDataSet, and the AMR "
"structure itself is described in the vtkAMRMetaData class stored internally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/refactor-amr-datamodel.md:13
msgid ""
"Another impactful change was the separation of vtkAMRInformation into "
"vtkAMRMetaData and vtkOverlappingAMRMetaData. This allow much simpler "
"handling of the Overlapping vs NonOverlapping case and clear separation of "
"responsibility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/refactor-amr-datamodel.md:17
msgid ""
"In the process many API were reworked for consistency and stability. "
"Backward compatibility was kept for many methods but certains became "
"redundant and are just no-op with a deprecation flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/refactor-amr-datamodel.md:21
msgid "Add Support for AMR of vtkRectilinearGrid"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/refactor-amr-datamodel.md:23
msgid ""
"The AMR data model now supports creating AMR of vtkRectilinearGrid thanks to "
"the refactoring and the introduction of vtkCartesianGrid."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/refactor-amr-datamodel.md:26
msgid ""
"For vtkNonOverlappingAMR, the usage is pretty straight forward, just use "
"`SetDataSet(level, idx, grid)` with coherent cartesian grids and it will "
"work out of the box. Type can be mixed too."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/refactor-amr-datamodel.md:29
msgid ""
"For vtkOverlappingAMR, types cannot be mixed. Just add vtkRectilinearGrid "
"but do not use SetSpacing or SetRefinementRatio as they do not make sense "
"for this type. Instead, bounds will be automatically used internally and the "
"API will just work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/refactor-amr-datamodel.md:32
msgid "Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/refactor-amr-datamodel.md:34
msgid ""
"Here is the exhaustive list. `AMR::` refer to any AMR class, new or already "
"present, for the sake of brevity. (vtkUniformGridAMR, vtkNonOverlappingAMR, "
"vtkOverlappingAMR, vtkAMRInformation, vtkAMRMetaData, "
"vtkOverlappingAMRMetaData)"
msgstr ""

